Package com.example.canada_geese.Models

Class MoodEventModel

java.lang.Object
com.example.canada_geese.Models.MoodEventModel
public class MoodEventModel extends Object
Represents a mood event with various attributes such as emotion, timestamp, emoji, color, and location data.

      public MoodEventModel(String emotion, String description, String timestamp, String emoji, int color, boolean hasTriggerWarning, boolean hasLocation, double latitude, double longitude)
      Constructs a MoodEventModel with the specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      emotion - the emotion associated with the event.
      description - a description of the event.
      timestamp - the timestamp of the event as a String.
      emoji - the emoji representation of the emotion.
      color - the color associated with the emotion.
      hasTriggerWarning - whether the event has a trigger warning.
      hasLocation - whether the event includes location data.
      latitude - the latitude of the event location.
      longitude - the longitude of the event location.
